annotationA: DNA primase large subunit; DNA primase is the polymerase that synthesizes small RNA primers for the Okazaki fragments made during discontinuous DNA replication. Plays a role in the fat facets (faf)-dependent cell- communications pathway; Belongs to the eukaryotic-type primase large subunit family
annotationB: Replication factor C 38kD subunit, isoform A; DNA clamp loader activity; ATPase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: DNA replication; neurogenesis
